  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study assess the accuracy of a blood pressure monitor designed to detect atrial
      fibrillation. Subjects use the blood pressure monitor on a daily basis for 30 days and
      compare the readings to an ECG done at the same time.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
